    "connected-title": "Stay Connected",
    "connected-text": "Time with family, friends, or community is more than social—it can protect heart health, reduce stress, and encourage healthy habits. Studies show that people with strong social ties have better blood sugar control and a lower risk of depression (<a href='https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC11293637/' target='_blank'>Systematic review, 2024</a>). Shared meals, walking groups, or gatherings at faith centers provide both emotional support and accountability for healthy living.",
